Package mb.web

Class Summary
StreamPipe Pipe of streams that contains two sides, both have inputs and outputs.
StreamReceiver Used by application to receive input.
StreamSender Used by application to send output.
StreamSide One side of the stream, contains input and output, and when connected to another side, input connects with output on the other side, and output connects to input from other side.
WebThread Extension of Thread class, that stores basic data used for networking.
WebThreadClient Abstract parent of server-side client and remote client.
WebThreadRemoteClient Client-side of the Tic Tac Toe application.
WebThreadServer Server for TicTacToe game.
WebThreadServerClient Sub-thread created by WebThreadServer in case any connection comes.
Xmlable Superclass of any object that is convertable to XML.
XmlPipe Extension of stream-pipe, used for XML.
XmlReceiver Receives XML files.
XmlSender Sends XML messages.
XmlTree Representation of XML message with use of tree, where single node can have dtd, name, value, unlimited attributes and unlimited children, of which every is also a node with the same properties.
